partialText:
[Cheonji Daily Washington = Reporter Eloise Lee], July 26 &mdash;

In the wake of President Biden&#39;s decision not to run for&nbsp;re-election, the White House is pushing a stoic, near-heroic portrayal of Biden.

A new instagram post featuring a still&nbsp;of Biden at the Resolute Desk in the Oval Office&nbsp;when he addressed the nation this week,&nbsp;is accompanied by a quote from the speech:


<img alt="ⓒ천지일보 2024.07.27.  The White House's official Instagram account posted a sombre image of President Biden with the message to &quot;Keep the faith&quot; following his decision to stand down for re-election." src="https://www.newscj.com/news/photo/202407/3163505_3199787_1247.png" />
ⓒ천지일보 2024.07.27. The White House&#39;s official Instagram account posted a sombre image of President Biden with the message to &quot;Keep the faith&quot; following his decision to stand down for re-election.



&quot;History is in your hands.
The power is in your hands.
The idea of Amrican is in your hands.
We just have to keep the faith and remember who we are.&quot;

The caption for the post was simply, &quot;Keep the faith.&quot;

In his address to the nation, Biden emphasized that the future of America and the ideals of Democracy are more significant than a single person or title, namely his.&nbsp;&nbsp;

Earlier in the week, another post confirmed&nbsp;the news of his decision to&nbsp;stand down.&nbsp;The caption noted that President Biden will not accept his&nbsp;party&#39;s nomination of him as candidate for the&nbsp;presidency &mdash; a far more dignified way to explain&nbsp;that he has, in fact, lost the confidence of voters and has dropped out.
